Title: ShowRunner: A Self-Producing Introduction
Author: ShowRunner Project
Draft date: April 2026
Source: github.com/qm/ShowRunner

= Runtime: approx. 60 seconds.
= This video was produced using the software it introduces.
= The narration was generated by Kokoro TTS, a plugin running inside ShowRunner.
= Every cue that triggered OBS, Ardour, and this script's own playback
= was entered into ShowRunner before this sentence was written.

# THE INTRODUCTION

[[Page boot]]

INT. TERMINAL -- NIGHT

A cursor blinks. One command:

    > sr start

ShowRunner boots. Fourteen plugins load.
One of them will generate this narration.
One of them is recording this screen right now.

# THE SYSTEM

[[Page paradox]]

INT. BROWSER -- CONTINUOUS

The dashboard opens. A script loads in the viewer.

This script.
The one you are watching.

NARRATOR (V.O.)
ShowRunner is the software
that produced this video about ShowRunner.
That is not a mistake.

[[Page system]]

The /script page. The colored markers in the text
are live cues -- orange for Lights,
blue for Sound, purple for Video.
They were placed here before we pressed record.

NARRATOR (V.O.)
A show is a script with intentions attached.
ShowRunner is where you attach them.

# THE META MOMENT

[[Page meta]]

INT. SHOWRUNNER UI -- CONTINUOUS

The ShowProgrammer panel. Cue 4.0.
Its notes field reads:
"This is the cue the viewer will watch fire."

NARRATOR (V.O.)
Right now, ShowRunner is managing
this recording session.
OBS is watching. Ardour is armed.
The script you are reading
was the production document.

A beat.

Cue 4.0 fires.
OBS cuts to this view.
ShowRunner writes to the cue log.

NARRATOR (V.O.)
That just happened.
You watched it happen.
ShowRunner watched it happen too.

# THE CLOSE

[[Page close]]

INT. TERMINAL -- MOMENTS LATER

The cue log:

    triggered_at   | duration_ms | notes
    [this moment]  | 1842        | Scene: Meta

NARRATOR (V.O.)
ShowRunner is the show
and the stage manager --
the script, the prompter, and the log.
This voice was rendered by a plugin.
This screen was captured by a cue.

    > sr cues list 1

Cue 99.0 -- WRAP -- status: fired.

NARRATOR (V.O.)
Fork it. Build something.

SUPER: "github.com/qm/ShowRunner"

FADE OUT.
